ExP NO:2

Aim
To implement student information management using OOP concepts in C, including encapsulation, data abstraction, and methods.

Algorithm:
Step-by-step approach:
Define a structure Student to store student information like:
Name
Roll number
Marks
Declare functions to perform operations on Student:
Input student data
Display student datCalculate total/average marks
Encapsulate operations using function pointers (simulating methods).#include <stdio.h>

PROGRAM:
#include <string.h>

// Define structure to simulate class
typedef struct Student {
    char name[50];
    int roll;
    float marks[3];

    // Function pointers to simulate methods
    void (*input)(struct Student*);
    void (*display)(struct Student*);
    float (*average)(struct Student*);
} Student;

// Function to input student data
void inputStudent(Student* s) {
    printf("Enter student name: ");
    scanf("%s", s->name);
    printf("Enter roll number: ");
    scanf("%d", &s->roll);
    for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        printf("Enter marks for subject %d: ", i+1);
        scanf("%f", &s->marks[i]);
    }
}

// Function to display student data
void displayStudent(Student* s) {
    printf("\nStudent Information:\n");
    printf("Name: %s\n", s->name);
    printf("Roll Number: %d\n", s->roll);
    for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        printf("Marks in Subject %d: %.2f\n", i+1, s->marks[i]);
    }
    printf("Average Marks: %.2f\n", s->average(s));
}

// Function to calculate average marks
float averageMarks(Student* s) {
    float sum = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        sum += s->marks[i];
    }
    return sum / 3;
}

// Main function
int main() {
    // Create student object
    Student s1;

    // Assign function pointers
    s1.input = inputStudent;
    s1.display = displayStudent;
    s1.average = averageMarks;

    // Call methods
    s1.input(&s1);
    s1.display(&s1);

    return 0;
}

Input:
Enter student name: John
Enter roll number: 101
Enter marks for subject 1: 85
Enter marks for subject 2: 90
Enter marks for subject 3: 80

Output:
Name: John
Roll Number: 101
Marks in Subject 1: 85.00
Marks in Subject 2: 90.00
Marks in Subject 3: 80.00
Average Marks: 85.00

Result:
   The program was executed sucessfully
